        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 8:37PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 837 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Burnsville, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Burnsville, Bakersville, Buladean, Bandana, Ramseytown, Micaville,
and Green Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
